00:45:39.600 --> 00:45:42.040
Giovanni Alfonso
Borelli's engravings

00:45:42.040 --> 00:45:45.640
from <i>De Motu Animalium</i>
, 1680 to 1681.

00:45:45.640 --> 00:45:49.250
And this volume is designed
to showcase humans and animals

00:45:49.250 --> 00:45:51.840
in various positions of
muscle exertion with an eye

00:45:51.840 --> 00:45:53.940
to physics rather than anatomy.

00:45:53.940 --> 00:45:55.240
And so what we're seeing

00:45:55.240 --> 00:45:57.080
in these illustrations
is the expansion

00:45:57.080 --> 00:46:00.820
of the enlightenment's
desire to classify and define

00:46:00.820 --> 00:46:03.390
and understand humanity through
representation and scale,

00:46:03.390 --> 00:46:04.690
which -- that's not new news.

00:46:04.690 --> 00:46:06.520
We've been hearing about that
throughout the presentations.

00:46:06.520 --> 00:46:09.820
So we've been digitizing
stuff like this.

00:46:09.820 --> 00:46:11.250
I'll show you a few
other examples.

00:46:11.250 --> 00:46:13.610
What you have here
is an illustration

00:46:13.610 --> 00:46:20.120
from Georg Bartisch's 1583 work,
<i>Ophthalmodouleia: Das ist,</i>

00:46:20.120 --> 00:46:23.530
<i>Augendienst </i>, and it
has I think 92 woodcuts.

00:46:23.530 --> 00:46:27.160
One here. And they're executed,
believed to have been executed

00:46:27.160 --> 00:46:29.040
by Hans Hemmerwahl
[assumed spelling]

00:46:29.040 --> 00:46:30.860
after Bartisch's own drawings.

00:46:30.860 --> 00:46:33.710
You can see here that -- I
think you can see in the shadows

00:46:33.710 --> 00:46:37.250
that there are super-imposed
flaps, so this is close

00:46:37.250 --> 00:46:39.210
to where -- you know we're
talking 16th century [inaudible]

00:46:39.210 --> 00:46:42.440
about the anatomy and
operation of the eye.

00:46:42.440 --> 00:46:45.830
I also, just in -- [inaudible]
remarkable, I also want to point

00:46:45.830 --> 00:46:49.920
out that despite or in addition
to its scientific merits,

00:46:49.920 --> 00:46:55.000
Bartisch was into, and a
believer in, things like magic,

00:46:55.000 --> 00:46:57.170
astrology, and witchcraft.

00:46:57.170 --> 00:46:59.130
And I don't -- I'm not
trying to knock him.

00:46:59.130 --> 00:47:02.090
I'm also not like advocating
for a belief in magic,

00:47:02.090 --> 00:47:03.950
but I want to point out
that when we're talking

00:47:03.950 --> 00:47:07.830
about the sciences, we're
talking about a kind of broad

00:47:07.830 --> 00:47:10.700
and varied terrain which
is constantly changing.

00:47:10.700 --> 00:47:13.440
My wife is a Classics Professor
and she wanted me to make sure

00:47:13.440 --> 00:47:16.440
that everyone was aware that
the word science is right

00:47:16.440 --> 00:47:19.150
from the Greek and Latin
for -- word for knowing.

00:47:19.150 --> 00:47:20.920
And so when we're talking
about science we're talking

00:47:20.920 --> 00:47:22.220
about forms of knowing.

00:47:22.220 --> 00:47:23.520
And I think that that will come

00:47:23.520 --> 00:47:25.650
across throughout a
number of the slides.

00:47:25.650 --> 00:47:27.180
